&lt;p>Made the drive out with my parents and my sister&amp;rsquo;s family. We found a local park in Ohio - the parking area did fill up but it wasn&amp;rsquo;t overwhelming crowds like I remember from when I drove to Oregon to see the eclipse in 2017. The infrastructure handled it.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>My year in photos (2023)</title><link>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2023/my-year-in-photos-2023/</link><pubDate>Sun, 31 Dec 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2023/my-year-in-photos-2023/</guid><description>&lt;p>2023 has been a stressful and hard year, and I have a sneaking suspicion this is a preview of even harder years on my path ahead. I am finding myself more tired and having really poor sleep quality, and I&amp;rsquo;m not sure I see things improving but I am cautiously optimisitic. I&amp;rsquo;ve been trying to keep positive by remembering my blessings as best I can, and this year came with a lot of blessings for sure. This post I do yearly forces me to acknowledge those blessings.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Video: Spring in Kyoto Revisited</title><link>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2020/video-spring-in-kyoto-revisited/</link><pubDate>Fri, 17 Jan 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2020/video-spring-in-kyoto-revisited/</guid><description>&lt;!-- &lt;video controls preload="metadata" poster="https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/videos/spring-in-kyoto.jpg">
