&lt;iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/586932947?h=c67825fca3" width="640" height="360" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen>&lt;/iframe>
&lt;p>A while back I posted an &lt;a href="https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2013/video-spring-in-kyoto-%E4%BA%AC%E9%83%BD%E3%81%AE%E6%98%A5/">old video I made of Spring in Kyoto&lt;/a>, but the audio track was removed by YouTube. So I&amp;rsquo;m self-hosting it here now, and reposting to revisit the memories!&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I really enjoy the atmosphere in this video, and I wish I made more videos like them. I used my Canon 7D for a lot of the video, but I wish it was shot in RAW video and on a tripod, as a lot of the detail was lost and a lot of the video ended up &amp;ldquo;wobbly&amp;rdquo;. There is also some software stabilization which looks pretty unnatural.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Plum Blossoms at Kitano Tenmangu Shrine in Kyoto, Japan (京都の北野天満宮)</title><link>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2020/plum-blossoms-at-kitano-tenmangu-shrine-in-kyoto-japan-%E4%BA%AC%E9%83%BD%E3%81%AE%E5%8C%97%E9%87%8E%E5%A4%A9%E6%BA%80%E5%AE%AE/</link><pubDate>Sat, 11 Jan 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2020/plum-blossoms-at-kitano-tenmangu-shrine-in-kyoto-japan-%E4%BA%AC%E9%83%BD%E3%81%AE%E5%8C%97%E9%87%8E%E5%A4%A9%E6%BA%80%E5%AE%AE/</guid><description>&lt;figure itemprop="image" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject" class="center landscape">
 
