&lt;p>Almost a year ago now I was lucky to be able to go back to my old stomping grounds in Kyoto, where I once studied Japanese in the hopes of maybe learning enough of the language to enroll in a university there to continue my studies in philosophy, perhaps being able to one day be another &amp;ldquo;professional&amp;rdquo; philosopher to walk along the &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosopher%27s_Walk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Philosopher&amp;#39;s Path&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>My year in photos (2019)</title><link>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2019/my-year-in-photos-2019/</link><pubDate>Tue, 31 Dec 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2019/my-year-in-photos-2019/</guid><description>&lt;p>In many ways this has been a strange and wonderful year, probably my most favorite year of my life to date. I traveled to Japan on a great flight deal, I hiked more than 1100 miles of the Appalachian Trail, and I drove across the USA on two (!) cross-country road trips, the latter a wonderful solo trip where I took my time photographing and visiting wonderful parks and museums.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>My year in photos (2016)</title><link>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2016/my-year-in-photos-2016/</link><pubDate>Sat, 31 Dec 2016 23:17:16 -0800</pubDate><guid>https://www.davidbcalhoun.com/2016/my-year-in-photos-2016/</guid><description>&lt;p>A few years back I put together my favorite photos of the year (see it: &lt;a href="//davidbcalhoun.com/2014/my-year-in-photos-2014/">part one&lt;/a> and &lt;a href="//davidbcalhoun.com/2014/my-year-in-photos-2014-part-2/">part two&lt;/a>). I decided to resurrect the tradition, and I hope to keep it going in the coming years!&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Onto the pics!&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="february">February&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>I visited Yosemite twice, first by myself and later with my friend Kevin.&lt;/p>
&lt;figure itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject" class="center">
