&lt;p>Image Source: &lt;a href="https://library.brown.edu/cds/perry/scroll7_Forkin.html">Brown University Library Center for Digital Scholarship&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>A long time ago, four black ships appeared off the coast of Japan, which had closed itself off from the world and its influences. These ships were from the US, and commanding them was Commodore Matthew C. Perry, who was instrumental in reopening Japan to the rest of the world&lt;sup id="fnref:1">&lt;a href="#fn:1" class="footnote-ref" role="doc-noteref">1&lt;/a>&lt;/sup>.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>